15:53.994 --> 15:54.828
[music stops]

15:54.912 --> 15:56.580
Yep, you're definitely annoying.

15:59.625 --> 16:01.043
People hate my song.

16:01.126 --> 16:04.588
No, they don't hate your song,
they hate my video.

16:05.047 --> 16:08.467
I guess I'm not your magic man,
I'm your tragic man.

16:10.844 --> 16:12.054
Just please take it down.

16:12.137 --> 16:15.474
OK, but I need a Gibbler Nibbler first.

16:15.557 --> 16:17.184
Even if it's a sad one.

16:18.310 --> 16:19.770
[Steph, lack-luster] Mmm...

16:24.858 --> 16:27.611
Man, Stephanie is so bummed.

16:27.695 --> 16:29.321
This is breaking my heart.

16:29.405 --> 16:31.573
There's gotta be some way
we can fix this.

16:36.954 --> 16:38.330
[laughs]

16:43.252 --> 16:45.129
Hey, are you thinking what I'm thinking?

16:45.963 --> 16:47.297
What are you thinking?

16:49.883 --> 16:52.803
That Tommy and Cosmo might be the answer.

16:53.470 --> 16:54.430
Then no.

16:57.433 --> 16:59.560
Boys and girls,

16:59.643 --> 17:03.105
this egg was organically laid

17:03.188 --> 17:07.901
by my happy, healthy,
free-range chickens.

17:07.985 --> 17:10.070
[cheering]

17:10.154 --> 17:11.488
Cue the chickens.

17:12.114 --> 17:18.704
Meet Jesse, Joey, Danny and Becky!

17:18.787 --> 17:19.830
-[cheering]
-[country music plays]

17:19.913 --> 17:23.042
Uh-oh, you know what that means?

17:23.125 --> 17:26.170
That means everybody chicken dance!

17:27.671 --> 17:28.630
And...

17:29.506 --> 17:30.758
[all cluck]

17:33.635 --> 17:34.470
[all cluck]

17:39.975 --> 17:42.269
You are working those overalls.

17:42.352 --> 17:44.396
OshKosh B'Gosh!

17:51.695 --> 17:52.654
Morning, Spot.

17:52.738 --> 17:53.697
Hola, Spot.

17:54.531 --> 17:55.908
Spot?

17:57.618 --> 17:58.952
Dios mio, he's gone!

18:00.037 --> 18:02.331
What are the chances
we're ever gonna find him?

18:02.873 --> 18:04.041
[kid shouts] Spider!

18:06.335 --> 18:07.669
I'd say pretty good.

18:08.670 --> 18:09.546
[all screaming]

18:09.630 --> 18:11.799
People, people...

18:11.882 --> 18:13.175
Why all the commotion?

18:16.512 --> 18:19.556
Hey, Max, there's a spider on your head.

18:21.183 --> 18:22.184
What?

18:23.560 --> 18:25.479
-[kid] Spider!
-[screaming continues]

18:31.652 --> 18:33.112
Mommy.

18:33.654 --> 18:34.947
I'm flying in, Max.

18:35.030 --> 18:37.658
Do not move.

18:37.741 --> 18:40.619
-Mom, wait!
-Don't hurt that spider!

18:40.702 --> 18:44.540
-I'll hold the terrarium, you flick.
-No, I'll hold the terrarium, you flick.

18:44.623 --> 18:48.001
I don't care who holds or who flicks.

18:48.085 --> 18:49.419
Just freaking flick!

18:50.879 --> 18:52.256
[Jackson whines nervously]

18:52.339 --> 18:53.340
[all gasp]

18:56.385 --> 18:57.803
Max, are you OK?

18:58.804 --> 18:59.721
Say something.

19:00.389 --> 19:01.431
OK.

19:01.515 --> 19:03.058
[screams]

19:05.811 --> 19:06.687
[gasps]

19:06.770 --> 19:09.064
Aw, that's so nice!

19:09.148 --> 19:11.525
You took Spot out on his morning walk.

19:13.277 --> 19:14.361
Of course we did.

19:14.778 --> 19:16.530
We love the little fellow. Here.

19:19.116 --> 19:21.952
Well, that was some presentation.

19:22.035 --> 19:24.037
Oh, no, wait,
we still have our big finish.

19:24.621 --> 19:25.831
Of course you do.

19:29.626 --> 19:31.503
And in conclusion,

19:31.587 --> 19:34.506
let's make Earth great again!

19:34.590 --> 19:35.549
Cue fire.

19:37.134 --> 19:38.635
[all] Ooh...

19:41.597 --> 19:42.639
Nailed it.

19:44.349 --> 19:47.811
Hey, Mom, I'm all better.
I can do the big finish.

19:47.895 --> 19:50.564
Oh, you're too late. I just nailed it.

19:52.107 --> 19:54.026
I don't know how
I'm going to choose a winner,

19:54.109 --> 19:56.862
but for 38K a year, that's my job.

19:58.906 --> 20:00.240
Get ready to lose.

20:00.324 --> 20:02.284
[sighs] I was born ready.

20:04.161 --> 20:05.704
To win, not to lose.

20:06.330 --> 20:08.207
This insult thing is so hard.

20:09.124 --> 20:12.044
Well, we've seen
some amazing presentations,

20:12.127 --> 20:16.089
but the title of this project was
One Kid Can Make A Difference,

20:16.173 --> 20:17.841
not One Kid, Their Parents

20:17.925 --> 20:22.262
and Some Strange But Handsome Latin Man
Can Make A Difference.

20:25.557 --> 20:29.186
Thank you for recognizing my contribution.

20:30.854 --> 20:32.189
Oh, I recognized. [giggles]

20:34.733 --> 20:35.651
Where was I?

20:35.734 --> 20:36.652
Oh. Yeah.

20:37.277 --> 20:39.613
The green ribbon goes to...

20:41.406 --> 20:45.410
Sarah, whose Barbie doll windmill
really blew me away.

20:46.245 --> 20:47.579
[cheering and clapping]

20:53.835 --> 20:57.714
The rest of the class will all get
second place participation ribbons.

20:57.798 --> 20:59.091
Class, back on the bus.

21:07.307 --> 21:08.141
Hey.

21:08.934 --> 21:11.645
This isn't over.
I'll see you at the Spring Science Fair.

21:12.396 --> 21:15.274
Well, bring your sunscreen
and put it on 30 minutes before

21:15.357 --> 21:17.025
'cause you're gonna get burned.

21:18.610 --> 21:19.444
Hey!

21:20.862 --> 21:22.364
That was actually pretty good.

21:23.782 --> 21:24.992
Thank you, Taylor's dad.

21:35.669 --> 21:37.045
What you doing, Max?

21:37.129 --> 21:38.213
My homework.

21:38.297 --> 21:40.215
And please. I don't need any help.

21:42.426 --> 21:46.680
Yeah, I got a little carried away.
I let Taylor's dad get under my skin.

21:46.763 --> 21:51.018
[sighs] I probably would have won
if you'd let me do it by myself.

21:52.060 --> 21:52.894
I know.

21:54.062 --> 21:56.523
Yeah, I'm sorry I made it all about me.

21:57.107 --> 22:00.319
You know, your project was really great

22:00.402 --> 22:03.155
and you taught our family
so many ways to help the planet.

22:03.238 --> 22:05.073
You really did make a difference.

22:05.991 --> 22:07.117
Are you still mad at me?

22:07.784 --> 22:10.203
I'm not mad, I'm just disappointed.

22:12.581 --> 22:15.375
And I hope you learned a good lesson,
young lady.

22:17.794 --> 22:18.670
I did.

22:19.296 --> 22:20.630
And I feel really bad.

22:21.131 --> 22:23.133
Bad enough to raise my allowance?

22:24.926 --> 22:27.220
Mmm... No.

22:28.388 --> 22:30.182
Hey, I gave it a shot.

22:32.476 --> 22:36.355
Green ribbon or not,
in my book, you are always a winner.

22:38.065 --> 22:39.566
I love you so much.

22:40.901 --> 22:42.194
I love you too, Mommy.

22:44.571 --> 22:46.490
Hey, I have
a few hours of homework left,

22:46.573 --> 22:47.991
can I have another Red Bull?

22:50.869 --> 22:53.371
I am starting to crash...

22:56.333 --> 22:58.585
Absolutely not.

22:59.336 --> 23:01.046
See? I'm a good parent again.

23:03.590 --> 23:05.592
All right, all right, I'm here.
What is it?

23:05.675 --> 23:06.676
Have a seat.

23:07.260 --> 23:08.095
OK.

23:08.178 --> 23:11.848
So, we were thinking about how you said
that people don't really like your song--

23:11.932 --> 23:14.059
I know what you guys are gonna say, OK?

23:14.142 --> 23:16.311
That I shouldn't give up, blah, blah...

23:16.394 --> 23:20.107
I should keep going, blah, blah...
The journey's more important than the...

23:20.190 --> 23:21.233
[snores]

23:23.944 --> 23:25.070
Wake up!

23:25.904 --> 23:27.280
We got something to show you.

23:29.324 --> 23:31.827
[Kimmy's voice]
Gibbler Style Party Planning presents...

23:31.910 --> 23:33.328
A Kimmy Gibbler production.

23:33.662 --> 23:36.206
Paid for by the
Kimberly Louise Gibbler Foundation.

23:36.289 --> 23:38.834
♪ Used to think I was unlucky in love ♪

23:40.168 --> 23:43.755
♪ Lonely days
What my nights were made of ♪

23:43.839 --> 23:47.259
♪ Broken hearts and lots of empty wishes ♪

23:47.592 --> 23:50.887
♪ Tired of wasting all of my best kisses ♪

23:51.304 --> 23:53.932
♪ Ooh-ooh-ooh-ooh ♪

23:54.015 --> 23:55.600
♪ Opposites attract ♪

23:55.684 --> 23:57.769
♪ Perfectly mismatched ♪

23:58.645 --> 24:01.189
♪ Ooh-ooh-ooh-ooh ♪

24:01.273 --> 24:03.191
♪ We were black and white ♪

24:03.275 --> 24:05.986
♪ Now it seems so right ♪

24:06.069 --> 24:09.114
♪ Hey, hey, the boy next door ♪

24:09.197 --> 24:13.326
♪ You could be the love
I've searched everywhere for ♪

24:13.410 --> 24:16.663
♪ Hey, hey, the boy next door ♪

24:16.746 --> 24:20.208
♪ Who'd have ever thought
it'd be him I would adore? ♪

24:20.292 --> 24:23.295
♪ The boy next door ♪

24:26.089 --> 24:29.259
♪ What's keeping me
from just running away? ♪

24:29.759 --> 24:33.555
♪ That's what I do
so what's making me stay? ♪

24:33.638 --> 24:36.391
♪ Used to think
he was just wasting my time... ♪

24:36.474 --> 24:37.559
[music stops]

24:37.642 --> 24:41.188
You guys, you just replaced me and Jimmy
with a dog and a baby.

24:41.271 --> 24:42.355
You bet I did.

24:44.858 --> 24:47.319
You're pandering
to the lowest common denominator.

24:47.402 --> 24:50.155
It's got over 300,000 views.

24:51.781 --> 24:53.575
You know, it's growing on me.

24:54.826 --> 24:56.203
Your song is a hit.

24:56.286 --> 24:59.456
Wow, I can't believe
that hundreds of thousands of people

24:59.539 --> 25:01.082
are listening to my song.

25:01.791 --> 25:03.293
It's a dream come true!

25:03.376 --> 25:06.671
Yeah, our magic is back
and my nose is lonely.

25:07.297 --> 25:08.965
[both giggle cutely]

25:09.049 --> 25:11.218
Yeah, you guys really are annoying.

25:14.137 --> 25:15.972
Jimmy, Kimmy, thank you.

25:16.514 --> 25:19.768
You Gibblers really came through for me.
I don't know what to say.

25:20.393 --> 25:22.646
How about, "Kimmy, you're a genius."

25:23.396 --> 25:24.564
Kimmy, you're a genius.

25:24.648 --> 25:25.857
"And you're beautiful."

25:26.483 --> 25:27.651
And you're beautiful.

25:27.734 --> 25:30.237
And you've always secretly
wished you were me.

25:33.657 --> 25:36.243
Fine, you don't have to say it out loud.

25:36.326 --> 25:37.285
I know.

25:40.288 --> 25:42.415
Now give me a Gibbler Nibbler.

25:42.499 --> 25:43.541
[Steph groans]

25:50.590 --> 25:52.509
♪ One, two, three, four... ♪

25:52.592 --> 25:54.427
[theme tune plays]
